This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on paraphrase generation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper proposes a deep generative model that uses a Wasserstein GAN, which is a popular technique in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The model also uses an encoder-decoder architecture, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of a transcoder, which is a type of neural network that can be used for various tasks such as image and speech recognition, and falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the model's performance using automatic metrics and human evaluation, which involves analyzing the generated paraphrases, a task that can be related to computer vision (cs.CV).
